text: The spotted moray eel (Gymnothorax isingteena) is a moray eel found in coral reefs in the Pacific and Indian Oceans.Gymnothorax isingteena at www.fishbase.org. It was first named by John Richardson in 1845.Common names for Gymnothorax isingteena at www.fishbase.org. ==References== ==External links== * isingteena Category:Fish described in 1845
